description: Zr₂N₂S crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to four equivalent N(1)³⁻ and three equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. There are three shorter (2.151 Å) and one longer (2.199 Å) Zr(1)-N(1) bond length. All Zr(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.843 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form NZr₄ tetrahedra that share corners with six equivalent S(1)Zr₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent N(1)Zr₄ tetrahedra, edges with three equivalent S(1)Zr₆ octahedra, and edges with three equivalent N(1)Zr₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 30-48°. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form distorted SZr₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent N(1)Zr₄ tetrahedra, edges with six equivalent S(1)Zr₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent N(1)Zr₄ tetrahedra.

Ba(AgS)₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form BaS₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Ag(1)S₄ tetrahedra, edges with six equivalent Ba(1)S₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Ag(1)S₄ tetrahedra. All Ba(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 3.164 Å. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form AgS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with six equivalent Ba(1)S₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent Ag(1)S₄ tetrahedra, edges with three equivalent Ba(1)S₆ octahedra, and edges with three equivalent Ag(1)S₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 18-54°. There is one shorter (2.686 Å) and three longer (2.696 Å) Ag(1)-S(1) bond lengths. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and four equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing SBa₃Ag₄ pentagonal bipyramids.

Sr₂C(NCl)₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to three equivalent N(1)³⁻ and four equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (2.630 Å) and one longer (2.653 Å) Sr(1)-N(1) bond length. There are a spread of Sr(1)-Cl(1) bond distances ranging from 3.038-3.053 Å. C(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms. Both C(1)-N(1) bond lengths are 1.239 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ and one C(1)⁴⁺ atom to form distorted NSr₃C tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent N(1)Sr₃C tetrahedra, corners with ten equivalent Cl(1)Sr₄ tetrahedra,  an edgeedge with one Cl(1)Sr₄ tetrahedra, and edges with two equivalent N(1)Sr₃C tetrahedra. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ atoms to form ClSr₄ tetrahedra that share corners with six equivalent Cl(1)Sr₄ tetrahedra, corners with ten equivalent N(1)Sr₃C tetrahedra,  an edgeedge with one N(1)Sr₃C tetrahedra, and edges with three equivalent Cl(1)Sr₄ tetrahedra.

LaOF crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. La(1)³⁺ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. All La(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.400 Å. All La(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.643 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent La(1)³⁺ atoms to form distorted OLa₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent O(1)La₄ tetrahedra, corners with twelve equivalent F(1)La₄ tetrahedra, edges with two equivalent F(1)La₄ tetrahedra, and edges with four equivalent O(1)La₄ tetrahedra. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent La(1)³⁺ atoms to form distorted FLa₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent F(1)La₄ tetrahedra, corners with twelve equivalent O(1)La₄ tetrahedra, edges with two equivalent O(1)La₄ tetrahedra, and edges with four equivalent F(1)La₄ tetrahedra.

BaTeO₃ is Potassium chlorate structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to one O(2)²⁻ and six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. The Ba(1)-O(2) bond length is 2.939 Å. There are a spread of Ba(1)-O(1) bond distances ranging from 2.799-2.883 Å. Te(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a distorted rectangular see-saw-like geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and two equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. Both Te(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.897 Å. There is one shorter (1.897 Å) and one longer (2.803 Å) Te(1)-O(2) bond length. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to one Ba(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Te(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the second O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one Te(1)⁴⁺ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OBa₃Te tetrahedra.

NaAgO crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a see-saw-like geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (2.363 Å) and two longer (2.395 Å) Na(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Ag(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.096 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Na(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing ONa₄Ag₂ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 2-14°.

RbSO₂F crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ and three equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are a spread of Rb(1)-O(1) bond distances ranging from 3.029-3.161 Å. There is one shorter (3.001 Å) and two longer (3.281 Å) Rb(1)-F(1) bond lengths. S(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and one F(1)¹⁻ atom. Both S(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.480 Å. The S(1)-F(1) bond length is 1.833 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to three equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and one S(1)⁴⁺ atom. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and one S(1)⁴⁺ atom.

CaTe is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing CaTe₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Ca(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.199 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing TeCa₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

CuBr is Zincblende, Sphalerite structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing CuBr₄ tetrahedra. All Cu(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.468 Å. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Cu(1)¹⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing BrCu₄ tetrahedra.

RbS is alpha boron-derived structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P̅62m space group. There are two inequivalent Rb¹⁺ sites. In the first Rb¹⁺ site, Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to two equivalent S(2)¹⁻ and four equivalent S(1)¹⁻ atoms. Both Rb(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 3.403 Å. All Rb(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 3.305 Å. In the second Rb¹⁺ site, Rb(2)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to two equivalent S(2)¹⁻ and four equivalent S(1)¹⁻ atoms. Both Rb(2)-S(2) bond lengths are 3.396 Å. All Rb(2)-S(1) bond lengths are 3.520 Å. There are two inequivalent S¹⁻ sites. In the first S¹⁻ site, S(2)¹⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺, three equivalent Rb(2)¹⁺, and one S(2)¹⁻ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge, corner, and face-sharing SRb₆S pentagonal bipyramids. The S(2)-S(2) bond length is 2.128 Å. In the second S¹⁻ site, S(1)¹⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺, three equivalent Rb(2)¹⁺, and one S(1)¹⁻ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge, corner, and face-sharing SRb₆S pentagonal bipyramids. The S(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.142 Å.

CsOH crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmc2₁ space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to four equivalent H(1)¹⁺ and five equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (3.031 Å) and two longer (3.248 Å) Cs(1)-H(1) bond lengths. There are a spread of Cs(1)-O(1) bond distances ranging from 2.997-3.247 Å. H(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and one O(1)²⁻ atom. The H(1)-O(1) bond length is 0.980 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to five equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and one H(1)¹⁺ atom.

NbRuSb is half-Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Nb(1) is bonded to four equivalent Ru(1) and six equivalent Sb(1) atoms to form a mixture of distorted corner and face-sharing NbSb₆Ru₄ tetrahedra. All Nb(1)-Ru(1) bond lengths are 2.686 Å. All Nb(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.101 Å. Ru(1) is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Nb(1) and four equivalent Sb(1) atoms. All Ru(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 2.686 Å. Sb(1) is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Nb(1) and four equivalent Ru(1) atoms.

ZnSnP₂ is Chalcopyrite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42d space group. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form ZnP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Sn(1)P₄ tetrahedra. All Zn(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.404 Å. Sn(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form SnP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Sn(1)P₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra. All Sn(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.546 Å. P(1)³⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Sn(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing PZn₂Sn₂ tetrahedra.

PON₁ crystallizes in the orthorhombic I2_12_12₁ space group. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to two equivalent N(1)³⁻ and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing PN₂O₂ tetrahedra. Both P(1)-N(1) bond lengths are 1.574 Å. Both P(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.612 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to two equivalent P(1)⁵⁺ atoms. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted bent 150 degrees geometry to two equivalent P(1)⁵⁺ atoms.

Li₂CaSiO₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42m space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted LiO₄ trigonal pyramids that share corners with four equivalent Si(1)O₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent Li(1)O₄ trigonal pyramids. All Li(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.981 Å. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are four shorter (2.396 Å) and four longer (2.764 Å) Ca(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form SiO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with eight equivalent Li(1)O₄ trigonal pyramids. All Si(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.657 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Li(1)¹⁺, two equivalent Ca(1)²⁺, and one Si(1)⁴⁺ atom.

CuAlS₂ is Chalcopyrite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42d space group. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form CuS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Cu(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Al(1)S₄ tetrahedra. All Cu(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.319 Å. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form AlS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Al(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Cu(1)S₄ tetrahedra. All Al(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.278 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Cu(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing SAl₂Cu₂ tetrahedra.

KSb₂ is Magnesium tetraboride-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Sb(1)+0.50- and four equivalent Sb(2)+0.50- atoms. There are a spread of K(1)-Sb(1) bond distances ranging from 3.611-3.722 Å. There are two shorter (3.759 Å) and two longer (3.995 Å) K(1)-Sb(2) bond lengths. There are two inequivalent Sb+0.50- sites. In the first Sb+0.50- site, Sb(1)+0.50- is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to four equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Sb(2)+0.50- atoms. Both Sb(1)-Sb(2) bond lengths are 2.922 Å. In the second Sb+0.50- site, Sb(2)+0.50- is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to four equivalent K(1)¹⁺, one Sb(2)+0.50-, and two equivalent Sb(1)+0.50- atoms. The Sb(2)-Sb(2) bond length is 2.916 Å.

CsGeI₃ is (Cubic) Perovskite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R3m space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form CsI₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Cs(1)I₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Cs(1)I₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with eight equivalent Ge(1)I₆ octahedra. There are a spread of Cs(1)-I(1) bond distances ranging from 4.255-4.410 Å. Ge(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form GeI₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Ge(1)I₆ octahedra and faces with eight equivalent Cs(1)I₁₂ cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 12°. There are three shorter (2.795 Å) and three longer (3.336 Å) Ge(1)-I(1) bond lengths. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Ge(1)²⁺ atoms.

Ba₂ZrS₄ is (La,Ba)CuO4 structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ and five equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms. All Ba(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 3.369 Å. There is one shorter (3.099 Å) and four longer (3.560 Å) Ba(1)-S(2) bond lengths. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent S(2)²⁻ and four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing ZrS₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. Both Zr(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.594 Å. All Zr(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.505 Å. There are two inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded to five equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one Zr(1)⁴⁺ atom to form distorted SBa₅Zr octahedra that share corners with five equivalent S(2)Ba₅Zr octahedra, corners with twelve equivalent S(1)Ba₄Zr₂ octahedra, edges with eight equivalent S(2)Ba₅Zr octahedra, and faces with four equivalent S(1)Ba₄Zr₂ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-54°. In the second S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form distorted SBa₄Zr₂ octahedra that share corners with two equivalent S(1)Ba₄Zr₂ octahedra, corners with twelve equivalent S(2)Ba₅Zr octahedra, edges with two equivalent S(1)Ba₄Zr₂ octahedra, faces with four equivalent S(1)Ba₄Zr₂ octahedra, and faces with four equivalent S(2)Ba₅Zr octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-54°.

LiCoS₂ is Caswellsilverite-like structured and crystallizes in the triclinic P1 space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to three equivalent S(1)²⁻ and three equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms to form LiS₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Co(1)S₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Li(1)S₆ octahedra, and faces with two equivalent Co(1)S₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 48-50°. There are a spread of Li(1)-S(1) bond distances ranging from 2.576-2.626 Å. There are a spread of Li(1)-S(2) bond distances ranging from 2.584-2.615 Å. Co(1)³⁺ is bonded to three equivalent S(1)²⁻ and three equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms to form CoS₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Li(1)S₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Co(1)S₆ octahedra, and faces with two equivalent Li(1)S₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 48-50°. There are two shorter (2.286 Å) and one longer (2.288 Å) Co(1)-S(1) bond length. There are a spread of Co(1)-S(2) bond distances ranging from 2.285-2.288 Å. There are two inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Co(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Co(1)³⁺ atoms.

PbSe is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Pb(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing PbSe₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Pb(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 3.112 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Pb(1)²⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SePb₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

K₃InP₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Ibam space group. There are two inequivalent K¹⁺ sites. In the first K¹⁺ site, K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms. There are a spread of K(1)-P(1) bond distances ranging from 3.271-3.672 Å. In the second K¹⁺ site, K(2)¹⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms. All K(2)-P(1) bond lengths are 3.270 Å. In(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing InP₄ tetrahedra. All In(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.667 Å. P(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent K(2)¹⁺, four equivalent K(1)¹⁺, and two equivalent In(1)³⁺ atoms.

Sr(ZnP)₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form SrP₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra, edges with six equivalent Sr(1)P₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra. All Sr(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 3.077 Å. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form ZnP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with six equivalent Sr(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra, edges with three equivalent Sr(1)P₆ octahedra, and edges with three equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 23-51°. There are three shorter (2.472 Å) and one longer (2.534 Å) Zn(1)-P(1) bond length. P(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ and four equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms.

Li₃LaP₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. There are two inequivalent Li¹⁺ sites. In the first Li¹⁺ site, Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form LiP₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent La(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent Li(2)P₄ tetrahedra, edges with six equivalent Li(1)P₆ octahedra, faces with two equivalent La(1)P₆ octahedra, and faces with six equivalent Li(2)P₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 48°. All Li(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.946 Å. In the second Li¹⁺ site, Li(2)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form LiP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Li(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent La(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent Li(2)P₄ tetrahedra, edges with three equivalent La(1)P₆ octahedra, edges with three equivalent Li(2)P₄ tetrahedra, and faces with three equivalent Li(1)P₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 21-54°. There are three shorter (2.541 Å) and one longer (2.594 Å) Li(2)-P(1) bond length. La(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form LaP₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Li(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with twelve equivalent Li(2)P₄ tetrahedra, edges with six equivalent La(1)P₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Li(2)P₄ tetrahedra, and faces with two equivalent Li(1)P₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 48°. All La(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 3.036 Å. P(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Li(1)¹⁺, four equivalent Li(2)¹⁺, and three equivalent La(1)³⁺ atoms.

BeSiP₂ is Chalcopyrite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42d space group. The structure consists of four Be clusters inside a SiP₂ framework. In each Be cluster, Be(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to  atoms. In the SiP₂ framework, Si(1)⁴⁻ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)¹⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing SiP₄ tetrahedra. All Si(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.265 Å. P(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁻ atoms.

K₃Sb is Sodium arsenide structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. There are two inequivalent K¹⁺ sites. In the first K¹⁺ site, K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (3.600 Å) and three longer (3.987 Å) K(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths. In the second K¹⁺ site, K(2)¹⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms. All K(2)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.538 Å. Sb(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 11-coordinate geometry to three equivalent K(2)¹⁺ and eight equivalent K(1)¹⁺ atoms.

CsBrF crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Cs(1) is bonded to four equivalent Br(1) and five equivalent F(1) atoms to form distorted CsBr₄F₅ square pyramids that share corners with four equivalent F(1)Cs₅Br octahedra, edges with eight equivalent Cs(1)Br₄F₅ square pyramids, and faces with four equivalent Cs(1)Br₄F₅ square pyramids. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 125°. All Cs(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 3.813 Å. There is one shorter (2.973 Å) and four longer (3.124 Å) Cs(1)-F(1) bond lengths. Br(1) is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Cs(1), one Br(1), and one F(1) atom. The Br(1)-Br(1) bond length is 2.414 Å. The Br(1)-F(1) bond length is 2.488 Å. F(1) is bonded to five equivalent Cs(1) and one Br(1) atom to form FCs₅Br octahedra that share corners with four equivalent F(1)Cs₅Br octahedra, corners with four equivalent Cs(1)Br₄F₅ square pyramids, and edges with eight equivalent F(1)Cs₅Br octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 10°.

CdPt₃O₆ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmmm space group. There are two inequivalent Pt+3.33+ sites. In the first Pt+3.33+ site, Pt(1)+3.33+ is bonded to two equivalent O(2)²⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form PtO₆ octahedra that share corners with two equivalent Pt(1)O₆ octahedra, edges with four equivalent Cd(1)O₈ hexagonal bipyramids, and edges with two equivalent Pt(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 53°. Both Pt(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.043 Å. All Pt(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.070 Å. In the second Pt+3.33+ site, Pt(2)+3.33+ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Pt(2)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.011 Å. Cd(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form distorted CdO₈ hexagonal bipyramids that share edges with two equivalent Cd(1)O₈ hexagonal bipyramids and edges with eight equivalent Pt(1)O₆ octahedra. All Cd(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.532 Å. All Cd(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.327 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. ZrOS crystallizes in the cubic P2_13 space group. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ and three equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Ca₂NCl is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Ba₂CuO₂Br crystallizes in the trigonal R3m space group. Ba(1,2)²⁺ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent O(1)²⁻ and three equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. K₃Cu₃As₂ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. There are two inequivalent K¹⁺ sites. In the second K¹⁺ site, K(2)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form distorted KAs₆ cuboctahedra that share corners with six equivalent K(1)As₄ trigonal pyramids, edges with six equivalent K(2)As₆ cuboctahedra, and faces with six equivalent K(1)As₄ trigonal pyramids. All K(2)-As(1) bond lengths are 3.789 Å. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms. Both Cu(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.366 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to three equivalent K(2)¹⁺, four equivalent K(1)¹⁺, and three equivalent Cu(1)¹⁺ atoms.

Rb₂ZrF₆ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted RbF₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with six equivalent Rb(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra, corners with three equivalent Zr(1)F₆ octahedra, faces with eight equivalent Rb(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with three equivalent Zr(1)F₆ octahedra. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form ZrF₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Rb(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra and faces with six equivalent Rb(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra. All Zr(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.046 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to four equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and one Zr(1)⁴⁺ atom.

InPS₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅4 space group. In(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form InS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent P(1)S₄ tetrahedra. All In(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.526 Å. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form PS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent In(1)S₄ tetrahedra. All P(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.061 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to one In(1)³⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom.

Li₃Bi is alpha bismuth trifluoride structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. There are two inequivalent Li sites. In the first Li site, Li(1) is bonded to four equivalent Li(2) and four equivalent Bi(1) atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge, corner, and face-sharing LiLi₄Bi₄ tetrahedra. All Li(1)-Li(2) bond lengths are 2.917 Å. All Li(1)-Bi(1) bond lengths are 2.917 Å. In the second Li site, Li(2) is bonded in a 14-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent Li(1) and six equivalent Bi(1) atoms. All Li(2)-Bi(1) bond lengths are 3.368 Å. Bi(1) is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to six equivalent Li(2) and eight equivalent Li(1) atoms.

K₂AgAs crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms. There are a spread of K(1)-As(1) bond distances ranging from 3.442-3.616 Å. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms. Both Ag(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.573 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ atoms.

KLiZnO₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to two equivalent O(2)²⁻ and five equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both K(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.863 Å. There are a spread of K(1)-O(1) bond distances ranging from 2.882-3.040 Å. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to one O(1)²⁻ and three equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form LiO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent Li(1)O₄ tetrahedra, corners with four equivalent Zn(1)O₄ tetrahedra, edges with two equivalent Li(1)O₄ tetrahedra, and edges with two equivalent Zn(1)O₄ tetrahedra. The Li(1)-O(1) bond length is 2.128 Å. There are two shorter (1.947 Å) and one longer (1.997 Å) Li(1)-O(2) bond length. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and two equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form distorted ZnO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent Zn(1)O₄ tetrahedra, corners with four equivalent Li(1)O₄ tetrahedra,  an edgeedge with one Zn(1)O₄ tetrahedra, and edges with two equivalent Li(1)O₄ tetrahedra. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to five equivalent K(1)¹⁺, one Li(1)¹⁺, and two equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to two equivalent K(1)¹⁺, three equivalent Li(1)¹⁺, and two equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms.

RbPbCl₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Cl(2)¹⁻ and six equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms. Both Rb(1)-Cl(2) bond lengths are 3.308 Å. There are four shorter (3.470 Å) and two longer (3.689 Å) Rb(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths. In the second Cl¹⁻ site, Cl(2)¹⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Pb(1)²⁺ atoms to form distorted ClRb₂Pb₂ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Cl(2)Rb₂Pb₂ tetrahedra, corners with eight equivalent Cl(1)Rb₃Pb₂ trigonal bipyramids, and edges with six equivalent Cl(1)Rb₃Pb₂ trigonal bipyramids.

KScO₂ is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All K(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.732 Å. Sc(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing ScO₆ octahedra. All Sc(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.171 Å. Mg₂FeH₆ crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Mg(1)²⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent H(1)¹⁻ atoms to form MgH₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Mg(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Mg(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with four equivalent Fe(1)H₆ octahedra. All Fe(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 1.560 Å. H(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Mg(1)²⁺ and one Fe(1)²⁺ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge, corner, and face-sharing HMg₄Fe square pyramids.

CsYHgSe₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Se(1)²⁻ and six equivalent Se(2)²⁻ atoms. In the second Se²⁻ site, Se(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺, two equivalent Y(1)³⁺, and one Hg(1)²⁺ atom.

RbNO₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P3_121 space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to four equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and one N(1)³⁺ atom.

SrAgO₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(2)²⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SrO₆ octahedra. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Sr(1)²⁺, one Ag(1)²⁺, and one Ag(2)²⁺ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OSr₄Ag₂ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Sr(1)²⁺, one Ag(1)²⁺, and one Ag(2)²⁺ atom.

CdIn₂Te₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅4 space group. CaSnO₃ is Ilmenite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3 space group. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted CaO₆ pentagonal pyramids that share corners with nine equivalent Sn(1)O₆ octahedra, edges with three equivalent Ca(1)O₆ pentagonal pyramids, and  a faceface with one Sn(1)O₆ octahedra. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted see-saw-like geometry to two equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Sn(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

BaBiO₂I crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Ba(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.697 Å. There are two shorter (3.650 Å) and two longer (3.784 Å) Ba(1)-I(1) bond lengths. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms to form OBa₂Bi₂ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent O(1)Ba₂Bi₂ tetrahedra, corners with eight equivalent I(1)Ba₄ tetrahedra, and edges with four equivalent O(1)Ba₂Bi₂ tetrahedra. Ca₂Si is Cotunnite structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnma space group. There are two inequivalent Ca²⁺ sites. IrSb₂ is Marcasite-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/c space group. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 51-58°. There are a spread of Ir(1)-Sb(1) bond distances ranging from 2.699-2.715 Å. There are a spread of Ir(1)-Sb(2) bond distances ranging from 2.634-2.649 Å. There are two inequivalent Sb+1.50- sites. In the first Sb+1.50- site, Sb(1)+1.50- is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ir(1)³⁺ and one Sb(2)+1.50- atom. The Sb(1)-Sb(2) bond length is 2.887 Å. KLaS₂ is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 9°. All La(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.914 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent La(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SK₃La₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

LiBr is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing LiBr₆ octahedra. Cs₂SiF₆ crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. RbYO₂ is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Rb(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.943 Å. Y(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing YO₆ octahedra. All Y(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.337 Å. MgSiP₂ is Chalcopyrite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42d space group. The structure consists of four Mg clusters inside a SiP₂ framework. AlF₃ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3c space group. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing AlF₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 20°. AgInS₂ is Chalcopyrite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42d space group. All In(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.507 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent In(1)³⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing SIn₂Ag₂ tetrahedra.

HgIn₂Se₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅4 space group. BaF₂ is Fluorite structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. CaSe is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing CaSe₆ octahedra. RbPS₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Immm space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted q6 geometry to two equivalent S(1)²⁻ and eight equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms. KCaBi is Matlockite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. K(1) is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Bi(1) atoms. RbBr is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing RbBr₆ octahedra. RbAuI₃ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to three equivalent I(1)¹⁻ and six equivalent I(2)¹⁻ atoms. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 18-22°. Both Au(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.718 Å. All Au(1)-I(2) bond lengths are 2.702 Å. In the second Au²⁺ site, Au(2)²⁺ is bonded to two equivalent I(1)¹⁻ and four equivalent I(2)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted corner-sharing AuI₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 18-22°. Both Au(2)-I(1) bond lengths are 2.620 Å. All Au(2)-I(2) bond lengths are 3.373 Å. There are two inequivalent I¹⁻ sites. In the first I¹⁻ site, I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺, one Au(1)²⁺, and one Au(2)²⁺ atom. In the second I¹⁻ site, I(2)¹⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺, one Au(1)²⁺, and one Au(2)²⁺ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge, corner, and face-sharing IRb₃Au₂ square pyramids.

All Rb(1)-Br(2) bond lengths are 3.915 Å. There are four shorter (3.783 Å) and four longer (4.108 Å) Rb(1)-Br(1) bond lengths. Te(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Br(2)¹⁻ and four equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form TeBr₆ octahedra that share faces with eight equivalent Rb(1)Br₁₂ cuboctahedra. Both Te(1)-Br(2) bond lengths are 2.736 Å. All Te(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.736 Å. There are two inequivalent Br¹⁻ sites. In the first Br¹⁻ site, Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and one Te(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the second Br¹⁻ site, Br(2)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and one Te(1)⁴⁺ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing BrRb₄Te square pyramids.

K₃NO₃ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4cm space group. There are two inequivalent K¹⁺ sites. There is one shorter (2.593 Å) and one longer (2.676 Å) K(2)-O(2) bond length. All K(2)-O(1) bond lengths are 3.014 Å. N(1)³⁺ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both N(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.284 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to two equivalent K(2)¹⁺, four equivalent K(1)¹⁺, and one N(1)³⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent K(2)¹⁺ and four equivalent K(1)¹⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing OK₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-27°.

Rb₂Te₅ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to one Te(1)+0.40- and eight equivalent Te(2)+0.40- atoms. The Rb(1)-Te(1) bond length is 3.854 Å. RbTa(PO₄)₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(2)²⁻ and six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. KTlO is trigonal omega-derived structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of two KTlO sheets oriented in the (1, 0, 0) direction. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (2.700 Å) and one longer (2.756 Å) K(1)-O(1) bond length. Tl(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.382 Å) and two longer (2.482 Å) Tl(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Tl(1)¹⁺ atoms to form edge-sharing OK₃Tl₃ octahedra.

Sr₂NBr is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded to three equivalent N(1)³⁻ and three equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing SrBr₃N₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Sr(1)-N(1) bond lengths are 2.649 Å. All Sr(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 3.286 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ atoms to form edge-sharing NSr₆ octahedra. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ atoms.

Mg(PtO₂)₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmmm space group. Mg(1)²⁺ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. All Mg(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.420 Å. All Mg(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.189 Å. There are two inequivalent Pt+3.33+ sites. In the first Pt+3.33+ site, Pt(1)+3.33+ is bonded to two equivalent O(2)²⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing PtO₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 60°. Both Pt(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.069 Å. All Pt(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.053 Å. In the second Pt+3.33+ site, Pt(2)+3.33+ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Pt(2)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.989 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded to one Mg(1)²⁺, one Pt(2)+3.33+, and two equivalent Pt(1)+3.33+ atoms to form distorted OMgPt₃ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent O(2)Mg₂Pt₂ tetrahedra, corners with eight equivalent O(1)MgPt₃ tetrahedra, edges with two equivalent O(2)Mg₂Pt₂ tetrahedra, and edges with two equivalent O(1)MgPt₃ tetrahedra. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Mg(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Pt(1)+3.33+ atoms to form OMg₂Pt₂ tetrahedra that share corners with six equivalent O(2)Mg₂Pt₂ tetrahedra, corners with eight equivalent O(1)MgPt₃ tetrahedra,  an edgeedge with one O(2)Mg₂Pt₂ tetrahedra, and edges with four equivalent O(1)MgPt₃ tetrahedra.

Ba₂BiTaO₆ is Krennerite-derived structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3 space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to nine equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are a spread of Ba(1)-O(1) bond distances ranging from 2.765-3.111 Å. Ta(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form TaO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Bi(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 17°. All Ta(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.013 Å. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form BiO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Ta(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 17°. All Bi(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.364 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ba(1)²⁺, one Ta(1)⁵⁺, and one Bi(1)³⁺ atom.

SiO₂ is quartz (alpha) structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P3_221 space group. Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing SiO₄ tetrahedra. There are two shorter (1.626 Å) and two longer (1.629 Å) Si(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a bent 150 degrees geometry to two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

CuAlO₂ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Cu(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.880 Å. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing AlO₆ octahedra. All Al(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.923 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to one Cu(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OAl₃Cu tetrahedra.

YSF is Matlockite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. Y(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to five equivalent S(1)²⁻ and four equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are four shorter (2.825 Å) and one longer (2.853 Å) Y(1)-S(1) bond length. All Y(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.467 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing FY₄ tetrahedra.

KAg₂PS₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. There are four shorter (3.207 Å) and four longer (3.548 Å) K(1)-S(1) bond lengths. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted AgS₄ trigonal pyramids that share corners with four equivalent P(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent Ag(1)S₄ trigonal pyramids. All Ag(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.616 Å. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form PS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with eight equivalent Ag(1)S₄ trigonal pyramids. All P(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.068 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to two equivalent K(1)¹⁺, two equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺, and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom.

BaBiO₂Cl crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Ba(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.689 Å. There are two shorter (3.365 Å) and two longer (3.512 Å) Ba(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Bi(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.222 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms to form OBa₂Bi₂ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent O(1)Ba₂Bi₂ tetrahedra, corners with eight equivalent Cl(1)Ba₄ tetrahedra, and edges with four equivalent O(1)Ba₂Bi₂ tetrahedra. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ atoms to form ClBa₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Cl(1)Ba₄ tetrahedra, corners with sixteen equivalent O(1)Ba₂Bi₂ tetrahedra, and edges with four equivalent Cl(1)Ba₄ tetrahedra.

Ag₂HgSI₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmc2₁ space group. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded to one S(1)²⁻ and three equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing AgSI₃ tetrahedra. The Ag(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.603 Å. There are a spread of Ag(1)-I(1) bond distances ranging from 2.855-2.928 Å. Hg(1)²⁺ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to two equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.411 Å) and one longer (2.421 Å) Hg(1)-S(1) bond length. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Hg(1)²⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing SAg₂Hg₂ trigonal pyramids. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ atoms.

ScNiSb is half-Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Sc(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms to form ScSb₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Sc(1)Sb₆ octahedra, corners with twelve equivalent Ni(1)Sb₄ tetrahedra, edges with twelve equivalent Sc(1)Sb₆ octahedra, and faces with four equivalent Ni(1)Sb₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Sc(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.055 Å. Ni(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms to form NiSb₄ tetrahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Sc(1)Sb₆ octahedra, corners with twelve equivalent Ni(1)Sb₄ tetrahedra, and faces with four equivalent Sc(1)Sb₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 55°. All Ni(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 2.646 Å. Sb(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Sc(1)²⁺ and four equivalent Ni(1)¹⁺ atoms.

Ba(MgP)₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form BaP₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Mg(1)P₄ tetrahedra, edges with six equivalent Ba(1)P₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Mg(1)P₄ tetrahedra. All Ba(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 3.298 Å. Mg(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form MgP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with six equivalent Ba(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent Mg(1)P₄ tetrahedra, edges with three equivalent Ba(1)P₆ octahedra, and edges with three equivalent Mg(1)P₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 23-50°. There is one shorter (2.639 Å) and three longer (2.647 Å) Mg(1)-P(1) bond lengths. P(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and four equivalent Mg(1)²⁺ atoms.

Y₂TeO₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Y(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Te(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Y(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.460 Å. All Y(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.258 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OY₄ tetrahedra.

CsAuSe crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Au(1)¹⁺ and five equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Cs(1)-Au(1) bond lengths are 3.713 Å. There are a spread of Cs(1)-Se(1) bond distances ranging from 3.720-3.928 Å. Au(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted square co-planar geometry to two equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Au(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.463 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded to five equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Au(1)¹⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SeCs₅Au₂ pentagonal bipyramids.

Cs₂ZrO₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to three equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (3.093 Å) and two longer (3.550 Å) Cs(1)-O(1) bond lengths. There are two shorter (3.150 Å) and two longer (3.199 Å) Cs(1)-O(2) bond lengths. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to one O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. The Zr(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.945 Å. All Zr(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.127 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to six equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and one Zr(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted water-like geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

AlP is Wurtzite structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃mc space group. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing AlP₄ tetrahedra. There are three shorter (2.381 Å) and one longer (2.392 Å) Al(1)-P(1) bond length. P(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing PAl₄ tetrahedra.

FeAs₂ is zeta iron carbide structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnnm space group. Fe(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent As(1)+1.50- atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing FeAs₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 53°. There are two shorter (2.363 Å) and four longer (2.385 Å) Fe(1)-As(1) bond lengths. As(1)+1.50- is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Fe(1)³⁺ atoms.

BaN₃Cl crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to two equivalent N(2)+0.33-, three equivalent N(1)+0.33-, and four equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms. Both Ba(1)-N(2) bond lengths are 2.993 Å. There are two shorter (3.010 Å) and one longer (3.024 Å) Ba(1)-N(1) bond length. There are a spread of Ba(1)-Cl(1) bond distances ranging from 3.159-3.208 Å. There are three inequivalent N+0.33- sites. In the first N+0.33- site, N(1)+0.33- is bonded to three equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one N(3)+0.33- atom to form NBa₃N tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent N(1)Ba₃N tetrahedra, corners with ten equivalent Cl(1)Ba₄ tetrahedra,  an edgeedge with one Cl(1)Ba₄ tetrahedra, and edges with two equivalent N(1)Ba₃N tetrahedra. The N(1)-N(3) bond length is 1.193 Å. In the second N+0.33- site, N(2)+0.33- is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to two equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one N(3)+0.33- atom. The N(2)-N(3) bond length is 1.178 Å. In the third N+0.33- site, N(3)+0.33- is bonded in a linear geometry to one N(1)+0.33- and one N(2)+0.33- atom. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ atoms to form distorted ClBa₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Cl(1)Ba₄ tetrahedra, corners with ten equivalent N(1)Ba₃N tetrahedra,  an edgeedge with one N(1)Ba₃N tetrahedra, and edges with four equivalent Cl(1)Ba₄ tetrahedra.

LiNbO₂ is H-Phase structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form LiO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Nb(1)O₆ pentagonal pyramids, edges with six equivalent Li(1)O₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Nb(1)O₆ pentagonal pyramids. All Li(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.141 Å. Nb(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted NbO₆ pentagonal pyramids that share corners with six equivalent Li(1)O₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Li(1)O₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Nb(1)O₆ pentagonal pyramids. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 1°. All Nb(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.164 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Nb(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge, corner, and face-sharing OLi₃Nb₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-46°.

CaBiO₂Cl crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to one O(1)²⁻, three equivalent O(2)²⁻, and three equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms. The Ca(1)-O(1) bond length is 2.532 Å. There are two shorter (2.326 Å) and one longer (2.337 Å) Ca(1)-O(2) bond length. There is one shorter (2.835 Å) and two longer (3.148 Å) Ca(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to one O(2)²⁻ and three equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. The Bi(1)-O(2) bond length is 2.116 Å. There is one shorter (2.243 Å) and two longer (2.290 Å) Bi(1)-O(1) bond lengths. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded to one Ca(1)²⁺ and three equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms to form OCaBi₃ tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent O(2)Ca₃Bi tetrahedra, corners with two equivalent O(1)CaBi₃ tetrahedra, edges with two equivalent O(2)Ca₃Bi tetrahedra, and edges with two equivalent O(1)CaBi₃ tetrahedra. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and one Bi(1)³⁺ atom to form OCa₃Bi tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent O(2)Ca₃Bi tetrahedra, corners with two equivalent O(1)CaBi₃ tetrahedra, edges with two equivalent O(2)Ca₃Bi tetrahedra, and edges with two equivalent O(1)CaBi₃ tetrahedra. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms.

Li₄NCl crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. There are two inequivalent Li¹⁺ sites. In the first Li¹⁺ site, Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted rectangular see-saw-like geometry to one N(1)³⁻ and three equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms. The Li(1)-N(1) bond length is 1.937 Å. All Li(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.526 Å. In the second Li¹⁺ site, Li(2)¹⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms. All Li(2)-N(1) bond lengths are 2.126 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and six equivalent Li(2)¹⁺ atoms to form NLi₈ hexagonal bipyramids that share corners with six equivalent Cl(1)Li₆ octahedra and edges with six equivalent N(1)Li₈ hexagonal bipyramids. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 57°. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ atoms to form ClLi₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent N(1)Li₈ hexagonal bipyramids and edges with six equivalent Cl(1)Li₆ octahedra.

LiZnPS₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅4 space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form LiS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Zn(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent P(1)S₄ tetrahedra. All Li(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.461 Å. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form ZnS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Li(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent P(1)S₄ tetrahedra. All Zn(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.363 Å. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form PS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Li(1)S₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent Zn(1)S₄ tetrahedra. All P(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.062 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Li(1)¹⁺, one Zn(1)²⁺, and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom.

BaCaSn crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnma space group. Ba(1) is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Sn(1) atoms. There are a spread of Ba(1)-Sn(1) bond distances ranging from 3.623-3.822 Å. Ca(1) is bonded to four equivalent Sn(1) atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing CaSn₄ tetrahedra. There are a spread of Ca(1)-Sn(1) bond distances ranging from 3.271-3.340 Å. Sn(1) is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Ba(1) and four equivalent Ca(1) atoms.

BaS₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/c space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded to eight equivalent S(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing BaS₈ hexagonal bipyramids. There are a spread of Ba(1)-S(1) bond distances ranging from 3.182-3.286 Å. S(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one S(1)¹⁻ atom. The S(1)-S(1) bond length is 2.123 Å.

ZnF₂ is Rutile structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4₂/mnm space group. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing ZnF₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 50°. There are two shorter (2.066 Å) and four longer (2.075 Å) Zn(1)-F(1) bond lengths. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms.

BeGeAs₂ is Chalcopyrite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42d space group. Be(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form BeAs₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Be(1)As₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Ge(1)As₄ tetrahedra. All Be(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.268 Å. Ge(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form GeAs₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Ge(1)As₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Be(1)As₄ tetrahedra. All Ge(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.467 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Be(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Ge(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing AsBe₂Ge₂ tetrahedra.

K₂SiP₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Ibam space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of eight K clusters and two SiP₂ ribbons oriented in the (1, 0, 0) direction. In each K cluster, K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to  atoms. In each SiP₂ ribbon, Si(1)⁴⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent P(1)¹⁺ atoms. All Si(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.286 Å. P(1)¹⁺ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁻ atoms.

KSbP₂O₈ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3 space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All K(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.992 Å. Sb(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form SbO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent P(1)O₄ tetrahedra. All Sb(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 1.993 Å. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to one O(1)²⁻ and three equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form PO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Sb(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 44°. The P(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.490 Å. All P(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 1.577 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to three equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted bent 150 degrees geometry to one Sb(1)⁵⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom.

BaFI is Matlockite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to five equivalent I(1)¹⁻ and four equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are four shorter (3.635 Å) and one longer (3.894 Å) Ba(1)-I(1) bond length. All Ba(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.737 Å. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and four equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. All I(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 3.679 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and four equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and face-sharing FBa₄I₄ tetrahedra.

SKH₁ crystallizes in the trigonal R3m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to three equivalent H(1)¹⁺ and six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. All K(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 2.909 Å. There are three shorter (3.303 Å) and three longer (3.347 Å) K(1)-S(1) bond lengths. H(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to three equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and one S(1)²⁻ atom. The H(1)-S(1) bond length is 1.352 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to six equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and one H(1)¹⁺ atom.

CsPF₆ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form CsF₁₂ cuboctahedra that share edges with six equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra and edges with six equivalent P(1)F₆ octahedra. All Cs(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 3.301 Å. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form PF₆ octahedra that share edges with six equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra. Cu₃NbSe₄ is Sulvanite structured and crystallizes in the cubic P̅43m space group. IrSbS is Spinel-like structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pca2₁ space group. ZnGa₂Te₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅4 space group. Ca₄Bi₂O is (La,Ba)CuO4 structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. There are two inequivalent Ca sites. Na₃YCl₆ is Ilmenite-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3 space group. There are two inequivalent Na¹⁺ sites. All Ba(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 2.886 Å. Os(1)²⁻ is bonded to six equivalent H(1)+0.33- atoms to form OsH₆ octahedra that share faces with eight equivalent Ba(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra. All Os(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 1.744 Å. H(1)+0.33- is bonded to four equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one Os(1)²⁻ atom to form a mixture of edge, corner, and face-sharing HBa₄Os square pyramids.

CaPdF₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mcm space group. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Ca(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.406 Å. Pd(1)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Pd(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.019 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to two equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and one Pd(1)²⁺ atom.

Sr₄P₂O is (La,Ba)CuO4 structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. There are two inequivalent Sr²⁺ sites. In the first Sr²⁺ site, Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to five equivalent P(1)³⁻ and one O(1)²⁻ atom. There is one shorter (3.032 Å) and four longer (3.481 Å) Sr(1)-P(1) bond lengths. The Sr(1)-O(1) bond length is 2.823 Å. In the second Sr²⁺ site, Sr(2)²⁺ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Sr(2)-P(1) bond lengths are 3.248 Å. Both Sr(2)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.418 Å. P(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Sr(2)²⁺ and five equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ atoms. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ and four equivalent Sr(2)²⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing OSr₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

LiYS₂ is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form LiS₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Y(1)S₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Li(1)S₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Y(1)S₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Li(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.736 Å. Y(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form YS₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Li(1)S₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Li(1)S₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Y(1)S₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Y(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.742 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Y(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SLi₃Y₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

BaLiSb crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms. All Li(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 2.853 Å. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge, corner, and face-sharing BaSb₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 46°. All Ba(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.665 Å. Sb(1)³⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and six equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ atoms.

BaBeSiO₄ crystallizes in the monoclinic Cm space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 11-coordinate geometry to two equivalent O(3)²⁻, three equivalent O(2)²⁻, and six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Ba(1)-O(3) bond lengths are 2.865 Å. There is one shorter (2.720 Å) and two longer (3.255 Å) Ba(1)-O(2) bond lengths. There are a spread of Ba(1)-O(1) bond distances ranging from 2.834-3.288 Å. Be(1)²⁺ is bonded to one O(2)²⁻, one O(3)²⁻, and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form BeO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Si(1)O₄ tetrahedra. The Be(1)-O(2) bond length is 1.630 Å. The Be(1)-O(3) bond length is 1.632 Å. Both Be(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.626 Å. Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to one O(2)²⁻, one O(3)²⁻, and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form SiO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Be(1)O₄ tetrahedra. The Si(1)-O(2) bond length is 1.638 Å. The Si(1)-O(3) bond length is 1.641 Å. Both Si(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.639 Å. There are three inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ba(1)²⁺, one Be(1)²⁺, and one Si(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted bent 150 degrees geometry to three equivalent Ba(1)²⁺, one Be(1)²⁺, and one Si(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the third O²⁻ site, O(3)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted bent 150 degrees geometry to two equivalent Ba(1)²⁺, one Be(1)²⁺, and one Si(1)⁴⁺ atom.

BaAl₂Sb₂O₇ crystallizes in the trigonal R32 space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted BaO₆ pentagonal pyramids that share corners with six equivalent Al(1)O₄ tetrahedra. All Ba(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.816 Å. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to one O(2)²⁻ and three equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form AlO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Ba(1)O₆ pentagonal pyramids and  a cornercorner with one Al(1)O₄ tetrahedra. The Al(1)-O(2) bond length is 1.733 Å. All Al(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.786 Å. Sb(1)³⁺ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Sb(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.984 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to one Ba(1)²⁺, one Al(1)³⁺, and one Sb(1)³⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms.

Cs₂PtF₆ crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form CsF₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with four equivalent Pt(1)F₆ octahedra. All Cs(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 3.287 Å. Pt(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form PtF₆ octahedra that share faces with eight equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra. Cu₃VS₄ is Sulvanite structured and crystallizes in the cubic P̅43m space group. V(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form VS₄ tetrahedra that share edges with six equivalent Cu(1)S₄ tetrahedra. All V(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.219 Å. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form CuS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with eight equivalent Cu(1)S₄ tetrahedra and edges with two equivalent V(1)S₄ tetrahedra. RbZn₄P₃ is alpha bismuth trifluoride-derived structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/mmm space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent P(2)³⁻ atoms. CsNaSe is Matlockite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (3.767 Å) and four longer (3.773 Å) Cs(1)-Se(1) bond lengths. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing NaSe₄ tetrahedra. KAuSe crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Au(1)¹⁺ and five equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. Both K(1)-Au(1) bond lengths are 3.472 Å. There are a spread of K(1)-Se(1) bond distances ranging from 3.346-3.851 Å. RbBiO₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/c space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Li₅NCl₂ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. There are three inequivalent Li¹⁺ sites. In the first Li¹⁺ site, Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing LiCl₆ octahedra. All Li(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.582 Å. In the second Li¹⁺ site, Li(2)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted rectangular see-saw-like geometry to one N(1)³⁻ and three equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms. The Li(2)-N(1) bond length is 1.937 Å. All Li(2)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.527 Å. In the third Li¹⁺ site, Li(3)¹⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms. All Li(3)-N(1) bond lengths are 2.122 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Li(2)¹⁺ and six equivalent Li(3)¹⁺ atoms to form NLi₈ hexagonal bipyramids that share corners with six equivalent Cl(1)Li₆ octahedra and edges with six equivalent N(1)Li₈ hexagonal bipyramids. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 57°. LiGe₂N₃ is Enargite-like structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmc2₁ space group. The Ge(1)-N(2) bond length is 1.811 Å. There are two shorter (1.894 Å) and one longer (1.896 Å) Ge(1)-N(1) bond length. There are two inequivalent N³⁻ sites. In the second N³⁻ site, N(1)³⁻ is bonded to one Li(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Ge(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form NLiGe₃ tetrahedra that share corners with five equivalent N(2)Li₂Ge₂ tetrahedra and corners with seven equivalent N(1)LiGe₃ tetrahedra.

CsAuCdS₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmme space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Au(1)¹⁺ and eight equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. SrAlSiH crystallizes in the trigonal P3m1 space group. Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Si(1)⁴⁻ and three equivalent H(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Sr(1)-Si(1) bond lengths are 3.294 Å. All Sr(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 2.499 Å. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to three equivalent Si(1)⁴⁻ and one H(1)¹⁻ atom. All Al(1)-Si(1) bond lengths are 2.486 Å. The Al(1)-H(1) bond length is 1.751 Å. Si(1)⁴⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ and three equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms. H(1)¹⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ and one Al(1)³⁺ atom to form distorted corner-sharing HSr₃Al tetrahedra.

AlN is Wurtzite structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃mc space group. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing AlN₄ tetrahedra. IrSbS is Spinel-like structured and crystallizes in the cubic P2_13 space group. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 79°.

SrHOCl crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃mc space group. Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to three equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms. Ba₃Zr₂O₇ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. There are two inequivalent Ba²⁺ sites. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to one O(2)²⁻, one O(3)²⁻, and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form ZrO₆ octahedra that share corners with five equivalent Zr(1)O₆ octahedra and faces with four equivalent Ba(1)O₁₂ cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-1°. The Zr(1)-O(2) bond length is 2.151 Å. The Zr(1)-O(3) bond length is 2.117 Å. All Zr(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.129 Å. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 6°.

NaCuZrS₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent S(1)²⁻ and six equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms. Li₂Te is Fluorite structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing LiTe₄ tetrahedra. BaAg₂SnS₄ crystallizes in the orthorhombic I222 space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. Na₄OBr₂ is (La,Ba)CuO4 structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. There are two inequivalent Na¹⁺ sites. ZnO is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing ZnO₆ octahedra. CuYSe₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P3m1 space group. Both Na(1)-Au(1) bond lengths are 3.399 Å. There are a spread of Na(1)-Sb(1) bond distances ranging from 3.177-3.423 Å. Au(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to four equivalent Na(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ atoms. Both Au(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 2.706 Å. Sb(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent Na(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Au(1)¹⁺ atoms.

Cs₂Se is Fluorite structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing CsSe₄ tetrahedra. All Cs(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 3.683 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ atoms.

RbScO₂ is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Rb(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.862 Å. Sc(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing ScO₆ octahedra. All Sc(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.184 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Sc(1)³⁺ atoms.

KCl is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing KCl₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All K(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 3.192 Å. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded to six equivalent K(1)¹⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing ClK₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

CsAuBr₃ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ and eight equivalent Br(2)¹⁻ atoms to form CsBr₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Cs(1)Br₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Cs(1)Br₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with four equivalent Au(1)Br₆ octahedra, and faces with four equivalent Au(2)Br₆ octahedra. All Cs(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 3.992 Å. All Cs(1)-Br(2) bond lengths are 4.067 Å. There are two inequivalent Au²⁺ sites. In the first Au²⁺ site, Au(1)²⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ and four equivalent Br(2)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted AuBr₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Au(2)Br₆ octahedra and faces with eight equivalent Cs(1)Br₁₂ cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. Both Au(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 3.401 Å. All Au(1)-Br(2) bond lengths are 2.519 Å. In the second Au²⁺ site, Au(2)²⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ and four equivalent Br(2)¹⁻ atoms to form AuBr₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Au(1)Br₆ octahedra and faces with eight equivalent Cs(1)Br₁₂ cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. Both Au(2)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.464 Å. All Au(2)-Br(2) bond lengths are 3.088 Å. There are two inequivalent Br¹⁻ sites. In the first Br¹⁻ site, Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺, one Au(1)²⁺, and one Au(2)²⁺ atom. In the second Br¹⁻ site, Br(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺, one Au(1)²⁺, and one Au(2)²⁺ atom.

CaSO₄ is Zircon-like structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. S(1)⁶⁺ is bonded in a tetrahedral geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and two equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. Both S(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.489 Å. Both S(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 1.491 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and one S(1)⁶⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and one S(1)⁶⁺ atom.

LiZnAs is half-Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form LiAs₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Zn(1)As₄ tetrahedra, corners with twelve equivalent Li(1)As₄ tetrahedra, and edges with six equivalent Zn(1)As₄ tetrahedra. All Li(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.589 Å. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form ZnAs₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Li(1)As₄ tetrahedra, corners with twelve equivalent Zn(1)As₄ tetrahedra, and edges with six equivalent Li(1)As₄ tetrahedra. All Zn(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.589 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms.

Cd(AsO₃)₂ is beta Vanadium nitride-derived structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅31m space group. Cd(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form CdO₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent As(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 53°. All Cd(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.354 Å. As(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form AsO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Cd(1)O₆ octahedra and edges with three equivalent As(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 53°. All As(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.867 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to one Cd(1)²⁺ and two equivalent As(1)⁵⁺ atoms.

Ba₂ZrO₄ is (La,Ba)CuO4 structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(2)²⁻ and five equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Ba(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.920 Å. There is one shorter (2.664 Å) and four longer (3.008 Å) Ba(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing ZrO₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. Both Zr(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.145 Å. All Zr(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.125 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to four equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Zr(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the second O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded to five equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one Zr(1)⁴⁺ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OBa₅Zr octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-5°.

KInTe₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mcm space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms. All K(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.740 Å. In(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing InTe₄ tetrahedra. All In(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.863 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to four equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent In(1)³⁺ atoms.

Be₂C is Fluorite structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Be(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent C(1)⁴⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing BeC₄ tetrahedra. RbSH crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to three equivalent H(1)¹⁺ and six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. BaSe is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing BaSe₆ octahedra. SrI₂ is Baddeleyite-like structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnma space group. There are two shorter (3.334 Å) and one longer (3.365 Å) Sr(1)-I(2) bond length. There are a spread of Sr(1)-I(1) bond distances ranging from 3.404-3.490 Å. There are two inequivalent I¹⁻ sites. LiCaN crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnma space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing CaN₄ tetrahedra. There are a spread of Ca(1)-N(1) bond distances ranging from 2.443-2.487 Å. SiC is Moissanite-6H-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P3m1 space group. There are five inequivalent Si⁴⁺ sites. In the first Si⁴⁺ site, Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to one C(4)⁴⁻ and three equivalent C(2)⁴⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing SiC₄ tetrahedra. The Si(1)-C(4) bond length is 1.897 Å. All Si(1)-C(2) bond lengths are 1.894 Å. In the second Si⁴⁺ site, Si(2)⁴⁺ is bonded to one C(1)⁴⁻ and three equivalent C(5)⁴⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing SiC₄ tetrahedra.
