In the third Si⁴⁺ site, Si(3)⁴⁺ is bonded to one C(3)⁴⁻ and three equivalent C(1)⁴⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing SiC₄ tetrahedra. The Si(3)-C(3) bond length is 1.897 Å. All Si(3)-C(1) bond lengths are 1.894 Å. In the fourth Si⁴⁺ site, Si(4)⁴⁺ is bonded to one C(2)⁴⁻ and three equivalent C(3)⁴⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing SiC₄ tetrahedra. The Si(4)-C(2) bond length is 1.898 Å. All Si(4)-C(3) bond lengths are 1.895 Å. In the fifth Si⁴⁺ site, Si(5)⁴⁺ is bonded to one C(5)⁴⁻ and three equivalent C(4)⁴⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing SiC₄ tetrahedra. The Si(5)-C(5) bond length is 1.900 Å. All Si(5)-C(4) bond lengths are 1.895 Å. There are five inequivalent C⁴⁻ sites. In the first C⁴⁻ site, C(1)⁴⁻ is bonded to one Si(2)⁴⁺ and three equivalent Si(3)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing CSi₄ tetrahedra. In the second C⁴⁻ site, C(2)⁴⁻ is bonded to one Si(4)⁴⁺ and three equivalent Si(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing CSi₄ tetrahedra. In the third C⁴⁻ site, C(3)⁴⁻ is bonded to one Si(3)⁴⁺ and three equivalent Si(4)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing CSi₄ tetrahedra. In the fourth C⁴⁻ site, C(4)⁴⁻ is bonded to one Si(1)⁴⁺ and three equivalent Si(5)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing CSi₄ tetrahedra. In the fifth C⁴⁻ site, C(5)⁴⁻ is bonded to one Si(5)⁴⁺ and three equivalent Si(2)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing CSi₄ tetrahedra.

LiZnP is half-Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form LiP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra, corners with twelve equivalent Li(1)P₄ tetrahedra, and edges with six equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra. All Zn(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.493 Å. P(1)³⁻ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms.

LiBaH₃ is (Cubic) Perovskite structured and crystallizes in the cubic Pm̅3m space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent H(1)¹⁻ atoms to form LiH₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Li(1)H₆ octahedra and faces with eight equivalent Ba(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra. All Ba(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 2.842 Å. H(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to two equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ atoms.

CsNaTiO₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted rectangular see-saw-like geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. KYO₂ is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. ZrPtSi is half-Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Zr(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Si(1)⁴⁻ atoms. KLiTe is Matlockite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms. Sr₂AuBi is Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Sr(1) is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Au(1) and four equivalent Bi(1) atoms. BiB₃O₆ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2 space group. There are two inequivalent B³⁺ sites. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(3)²⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted BiO₆ pentagonal pyramids that share corners with four equivalent Bi(1)O₆ pentagonal pyramids and corners with two equivalent B(1)O₄ tetrahedra. Cs₂GeCl₆ crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. BaAgTeF is Parent of FeAs superconductors structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. RbTlO₂ is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Na₂ZnS₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Ibam space group. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to five equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to five equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and one Hg(1)²⁺ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OK₅Hg octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-16°.

Cs₂AuAgCl₆ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ and eight equivalent Cl(2)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted CsCl₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Cs(1)Cl₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Cs(1)Cl₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with four equivalent Ag(1)Cl₆ octahedra. All Cs(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 3.756 Å. All Cs(1)-Cl(2) bond lengths are 3.898 Å. Au(1)³⁺ is bonded in a distorted square co-planar geometry to four equivalent Cl(2)¹⁻ atoms. All Au(1)-Cl(2) bond lengths are 2.361 Å. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded to two equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ and four equivalent Cl(2)¹⁻ atoms to form AgCl₆ octahedra that share faces with eight equivalent Cs(1)Cl₁₂ cuboctahedra. Both Ag(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.402 Å. All Ag(1)-Cl(2) bond lengths are 2.911 Å. There are two inequivalent Cl¹⁻ sites. In the first Cl¹⁻ site, Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and one Ag(1)¹⁺ atom. In the second Cl¹⁻ site, Cl(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺, one Au(1)³⁺, and one Ag(1)¹⁺ atom.

CuAlO₂ crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Cu(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.882 Å. Al(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing AlO₆ octahedra. All Al(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.926 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to one Cu(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Al(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OAl₃Cu tetrahedra.

Na₂HgO₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded to five equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing NaO₅ square pyramids. There is one shorter (2.360 Å) and four longer (2.481 Å) Na(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Hg(1)²⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Hg(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.013 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to five equivalent Na(1)¹⁺ and one Hg(1)²⁺ atom to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing ONa₅Hg octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 0-17°.

LaZnOP is Parent of FeAs superconductors structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. La(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All La(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 3.363 Å. All La(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.374 Å. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing ZnP₄ tetrahedra. All Zn(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.500 Å. P(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent La(1)³⁺ and four equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent La(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OLa₄ tetrahedra.

Li₂CN₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mmm space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing LiN₄ tetrahedra. All Li(1)-N(1) bond lengths are 2.088 Å. C(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms. Both C(1)-N(1) bond lengths are 1.238 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and one C(1)⁴⁺ atom.

KCuHfS₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmcm space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to two equivalent S(2)²⁻ and six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. Both K(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 3.205 Å. There are four shorter (3.316 Å) and two longer (3.448 Å) K(1)-S(1) bond lengths. Hf(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent S(2)²⁻ and four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form HfS₆ octahedra that share corners with two equivalent Hf(1)S₆ octahedra, edges with two equivalent Hf(1)S₆ octahedra, and edges with four equivalent Cu(1)S₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 41°. Both Hf(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.602 Å. All Hf(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.578 Å. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded to two equivalent S(1)²⁻ and two equivalent S(2)²⁻ atoms to form CuS₄ tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent Cu(1)S₄ tetrahedra and edges with four equivalent Hf(1)S₆ octahedra. Both Cu(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.289 Å. Both Cu(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.331 Å. There are two inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to three equivalent K(1)¹⁺, two equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺, and one Cu(1)¹⁺ atom. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to two equivalent K(1)¹⁺, two equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺, and two equivalent Cu(1)¹⁺ atoms.

Sr₂Mg(BO₃)₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded in a distorted q6 geometry to three equivalent O(1)²⁻ and six equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.732 Å) and two longer (2.740 Å) Sr(1)-O(1) bond lengths. There are a spread of Sr(1)-O(2) bond distances ranging from 2.600-2.699 Å. Mg(1)²⁺ is bonded in an octahedral geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. Both Mg(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.159 Å. All Mg(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.100 Å. B(1)³⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to one O(1)²⁻ and two equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. The B(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.382 Å. Both B(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 1.398 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Sr(1)²⁺, one Mg(1)²⁺, and one B(1)³⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Sr(1)²⁺, one Mg(1)²⁺, and one B(1)³⁺ atom.

Cs₂SiAs₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Ibam space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms. There are a spread of Cs(1)-As(1) bond distances ranging from 3.632-4.043 Å. Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form distorted edge-sharing SiAs₄ tetrahedra. All Si(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.418 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

(K)₂PtH₆ is Fluorite structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of eight K clusters and four PtH₆ clusters. In each K cluster, K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to  atoms. In each PtH₆ cluster, Pt(1)²⁻ is bonded in an octahedral geometry to six equivalent H(1) atoms. All Pt(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 1.658 Å. H(1) is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Pt(1)²⁻ atom.

Ba₂LaTaO₆ is Orthorhombic Perovskite-derived structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3 space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to nine equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are a spread of Ba(1)-O(1) bond distances ranging from 2.753-3.155 Å. La(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form LaO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Ta(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 19°. All La(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.398 Å. Ta(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form TaO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent La(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 19°. All Ta(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.022 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ba(1)²⁺, one La(1)³⁺, and one Ta(1)⁵⁺ atom.

Ba(MgBi)₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. Ba(1) is bonded to six equivalent Bi(1) atoms to form BaBi₆ octahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Mg(1)Bi₄ tetrahedra, edges with six equivalent Ba(1)Bi₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Mg(1)Bi₄ tetrahedra. All Ba(1)-Bi(1) bond lengths are 3.602 Å. Mg(1) is bonded to four equivalent Bi(1) atoms to form MgBi₄ tetrahedra that share corners with six equivalent Ba(1)Bi₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent Mg(1)Bi₄ tetrahedra, edges with three equivalent Ba(1)Bi₆ octahedra, and edges with three equivalent Mg(1)Bi₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 19-52°. There is one shorter (2.995 Å) and three longer (3.000 Å) Mg(1)-Bi(1) bond lengths. Bi(1) is bonded to three equivalent Ba(1) and four equivalent Mg(1) atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing BiBa₃Mg₄ pentagonal bipyramids.

Y₂Si₂O₇ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. Y(1)³⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(3)²⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted YO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Si(1)O₄ tetrahedra and edges with three equivalent Y(1)O₆ octahedra. Both Y(1)-O(3) bond lengths are 2.275 Å. There are two shorter (2.266 Å) and two longer (2.338 Å) Y(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to one O(2)²⁻, one O(3)²⁻, and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form SiO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with six equivalent Y(1)O₆ octahedra and  a cornercorner with one Si(1)O₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 49-57°. The Si(1)-O(2) bond length is 1.648 Å. The Si(1)-O(3) bond length is 1.639 Å. Both Si(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.649 Å. There are three inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to two equivalent Y(1)³⁺ and one Si(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁺ atoms. In the third O²⁻ site, O(3)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to two equivalent Y(1)³⁺ and one Si(1)⁴⁺ atom.

Ba₂AuBi is Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Ba(1) is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Au(1) and four equivalent Bi(1) atoms. All Ba(1)-Au(1) bond lengths are 3.648 Å. All Ba(1)-Bi(1) bond lengths are 3.648 Å. Au(1) is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent Ba(1) atoms. Bi(1) is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent Ba(1) atoms.

Hg₂SnSe₄ crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅4 space group. There are two inequivalent Hg²⁺ sites. In the first Hg²⁺ site, Hg(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form HgSe₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Hg(2)Se₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent Sn(1)Se₄ tetrahedra. All Hg(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.729 Å. In the second Hg²⁺ site, Hg(2)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form HgSe₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Hg(1)Se₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent Sn(1)Se₄ tetrahedra. All Hg(2)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.730 Å. Sn(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form SnSe₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Hg(1)Se₄ tetrahedra and corners with four equivalent Hg(2)Se₄ tetrahedra. All Sn(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.592 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Hg(1)²⁺, one Hg(2)²⁺, and one Sn(1)⁴⁺ atom.

CuGaO₂ crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Cu(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.869 Å. Ga(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing GaO₆ octahedra. All Ga(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.016 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to one Cu(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Ga(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OGa₃Cu tetrahedra.

Ca₂CuZn₂P₃ crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded to three equivalent P(1)³⁻ and three equivalent P(2)³⁻ atoms to form CaP₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Ca(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra, edges with six equivalent Ca(1)P₆ octahedra, edges with three equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra, and  a faceface with one Ca(1)P₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 45°. All Ca(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.942 Å. All Ca(1)-P(2) bond lengths are 3.053 Å. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent P(2)³⁻ atoms. All Cu(1)-P(2) bond lengths are 2.335 Å. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form ZnP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with six equivalent Ca(1)P₆ octahedra, corners with six equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra, edges with three equivalent Ca(1)P₆ octahedra, and edges with three equivalent Zn(1)P₄ tetrahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 20-53°. There are three shorter (2.443 Å) and one longer (2.538 Å) Zn(1)-P(1) bond length. There are two inequivalent P³⁻ sites. In the first P³⁻ site, P(1)³⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and four equivalent Zn(1)²⁺ atoms to form distorted edge-sharing PCa₃Zn₄ pentagonal bipyramids. In the second P³⁻ site, P(2)³⁻ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and three equivalent Cu(1)¹⁺ atoms.

Ba₂MgH₆ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent H(1)¹⁻ atoms to form BaH₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with six equivalent Ba(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra, corners with three equivalent Mg(1)H₆ octahedra, faces with eight equivalent Ba(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with three equivalent Mg(1)H₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 24°. There are a spread of Ba(1)-H(1) bond distances ranging from 2.748-2.875 Å. Mg(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent H(1)¹⁻ atoms to form MgH₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Ba(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra and faces with six equivalent Ba(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra. All Mg(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 1.983 Å. H(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to four equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one Mg(1)²⁺ atom.

LiSrP crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms. All Li(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.532 Å. Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge, corner, and face-sharing SrP₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 46°. All Sr(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 3.236 Å. P(1)³⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and six equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ atoms.

CdSnP₂ is Chalcopyrite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal I̅42d space group. Cd(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form CdP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Cd(1)P₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Sn(1)P₄ tetrahedra. All Cd(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.599 Å. Sn(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form SnP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Sn(1)P₄ tetrahedra and corners with eight equivalent Cd(1)P₄ tetrahedra. All Sn(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.550 Å. P(1)³⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Cd(1)²⁺ and two equivalent Sn(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing PCd₂Sn₂ tetrahedra.

TiNiSn is half-Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Ti(1) is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Ni(1) and six equivalent Sn(1) atoms. All Ti(1)-Ni(1) bond lengths are 2.561 Å. All Ti(1)-Sn(1) bond lengths are 2.958 Å. Ni(1) is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Ti(1) and four equivalent Sn(1) atoms. All Ni(1)-Sn(1) bond lengths are 2.561 Å. Sn(1) is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Ti(1) and four equivalent Ni(1) atoms.

CsCuO crystallizes in the orthorhombic Ama2 space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted see-saw-like geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are a spread of Cs(1)-O(1) bond distances ranging from 3.086-3.204 Å. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Cu(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.841 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted L-shaped geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Cu(1)¹⁺ atoms.

SbNBa₃ crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ and two equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (3.835 Å) and two longer (4.091 Å) Ba(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths. Both Ba(1)-N(1) bond lengths are 2.709 Å. Sb(1)³⁻ is bonded to twelve equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ atoms to form SbBa₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with six equivalent Sb(1)Ba₁₂ cuboctahedra, corners with six equivalent N(1)Ba₆ octahedra, faces with eight equivalent Sb(1)Ba₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with six equivalent N(1)Ba₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 17°. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ atoms to form NBa₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Sb(1)Ba₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Sb(1)Ba₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with two equivalent N(1)Ba₆ octahedra.

Li₂SiO₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Cmc2₁ space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to one O(1)²⁻ and three equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form distorted LiO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with five equivalent Si(1)O₄ tetrahedra and corners with seven equivalent Li(1)O₄ tetrahedra. The Li(1)-O(1) bond length is 2.188 Å. There are a spread of Li(1)-O(2) bond distances ranging from 1.959-1.990 Å. Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and two equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form SiO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent Si(1)O₄ tetrahedra and corners with ten equivalent Li(1)O₄ tetrahedra. There is one shorter (1.700 Å) and one longer (1.703 Å) Si(1)-O(1) bond length. Both Si(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 1.611 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form distorted OLi₂Si₂ tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent O(1)Li₂Si₂ tetrahedra and corners with ten equivalent O(2)Li₃Si tetrahedra. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ and one Si(1)⁴⁺ atom to form distorted OLi₃Si tetrahedra that share corners with five equivalent O(1)Li₂Si₂ tetrahedra and corners with seven equivalent O(2)Li₃Si tetrahedra.

Sr₂RuH₆ crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent H(1)¹⁻ atoms to form SrH₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Sr(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Sr(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with four equivalent Ru(1)H₆ octahedra. All Sr(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 2.704 Å. Ru(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent H(1)¹⁻ atoms to form RuH₆ octahedra that share faces with eight equivalent Sr(1)H₁₂ cuboctahedra. All Ru(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 1.726 Å. H(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Sr(1)²⁺ and one Ru(1)²⁺ atom to form a mixture of edge, corner, and face-sharing HSr₄Ru square pyramids.

In₂O₃ is Corundum structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3c space group. In(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge, corner, and face-sharing InO₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 49-63°. There are three shorter (2.158 Å) and three longer (2.291 Å) In(1)-O(1) bond lengths. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent In(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OIn₄ trigonal pyramids.

NaInO₂ is Caswellsilverite structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3m space group. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form NaO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent In(1)O₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Na(1)O₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent In(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 8°. All Na(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.472 Å. In(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form InO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Na(1)O₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Na(1)O₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent In(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 8°. All In(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.237 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Na(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent In(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing ONa₃In₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

Cs₂ZrCl₆ crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms to form CsCl₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Cs(1)Cl₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Cs(1)Cl₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with four equivalent Zr(1)Cl₆ octahedra. All Cs(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 3.824 Å. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms to form ZrCl₆ octahedra that share faces with eight equivalent Cs(1)Cl₁₂ cuboctahedra. All Zr(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.494 Å. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and one Zr(1)⁴⁺ atom.

KH₂PO₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/c space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are a spread of K(1)-O(1) bond distances ranging from 2.781-2.961 Å. P(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted tetrahedral geometry to two equivalent H(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both P(1)-H(1) bond lengths are 1.429 Å. Both P(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.520 Å. H(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one P(1)¹⁺ atom. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to three equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and one P(1)¹⁺ atom.

FeSe₂ is Marcasite structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnnm space group. Fe(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Se(1)+1.50- atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing FeSe₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 57°. There are two shorter (2.369 Å) and four longer (2.380 Å) Fe(1)-Se(1) bond lengths. Se(1)+1.50- is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Fe(1)³⁺ atoms.

LiBaP crystallizes in the hexagonal P̅6m2 space group. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms. All Li(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.560 Å. Ga₂Te₅ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/m space group. Ga(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Te(1)+0.80- atoms to form edge-sharing GaTe₄ tetrahedra. All Ga(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.684 Å. CuYO₂ crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃/mmc space group. Y(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted edge-sharing YO₆ octahedra. All Y(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.302 Å. OsSb₂ is zeta iron carbide structured and crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pnnm space group. NaAlTe₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mcm space group. Na(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms. All Na(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.521 Å. RbAu₃Se₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted hexagonal planar geometry to six equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. All Rb(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 3.800 Å. TiPtSn is half-Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. description: ScF₃ is alpha Rhenium trioxide structured and crystallizes in the cubic Pm̅3m space group. Sc(1)³⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing ScF₆ octahedra. In the second Ca²⁺ site, Ca(2)²⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to four equivalent Sb(1)³⁻ and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. All Ca(2)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.283 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to two equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and four equivalent Ca(2)²⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing OCa₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

BaSeO₃ is Potassium chlorate structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to three equivalent O(2)²⁻ and six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.842 Å) and two longer (3.178 Å) Ba(1)-O(2) bond lengths. There are a spread of Ba(1)-O(1) bond distances ranging from 2.823-2.889 Å. Se(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one O(2)²⁻ and two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. The Se(1)-O(2) bond length is 1.727 Å. Both Se(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.731 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one Se(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Ba(1)²⁺ and one Se(1)⁴⁺ atom to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OBa₃Se tetrahedra.

ZrNiSn is half-Heusler structured and crystallizes in the cubic F̅43m space group. Zr(1) is bonded in a 10-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Ni(1) and six equivalent Sn(1) atoms. All Zr(1)-Ni(1) bond lengths are 2.669 Å. All Zr(1)-Sn(1) bond lengths are 3.081 Å. Ni(1) is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to four equivalent Zr(1) and four equivalent Sn(1) atoms. All Ni(1)-Sn(1) bond lengths are 2.669 Å. Sn(1) is bonded in a distorted q6 geometry to six equivalent Zr(1) and four equivalent Ni(1) atoms.

Ca(BeN)₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal I4/mcm space group. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to eight equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms. All Ca(1)-N(1) bond lengths are 2.692 Å. Be(1)²⁺ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent N(1)³⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (1.606 Å) and two longer (1.661 Å) Be(1)-N(1) bond lengths. N(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ and three equivalent Be(1)²⁺ atoms.

KBr is Halite, Rock Salt structured and crystallizes in the cubic Fm̅3m space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing KBr₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All K(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 3.352 Å. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded to six equivalent K(1)¹⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing BrK₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

LaCoN₃ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. La(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to two equivalent N(3)+1.67- and three equivalent N(1)+1.67- atoms. Both La(1)-N(3) bond lengths are 2.813 Å. There is one shorter (2.423 Å) and two longer (2.468 Å) La(1)-N(1) bond lengths. Co(1)²⁺ is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to one N(2)+1.67- and two equivalent N(1)+1.67- atoms. The Co(1)-N(2) bond length is 1.683 Å. There is one shorter (1.859 Å) and one longer (1.915 Å) Co(1)-N(1) bond length. There are three inequivalent N+1.67- sites. In the first N+1.67- site, N(1)+1.67- is bonded to three equivalent La(1)³⁺ and two equivalent Co(1)²⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing NLa₃Co₂ trigonal bipyramids. In the second N+1.67- site, N(2)+1.67- is bonded in a 1-coordinate geometry to one Co(1)²⁺ and one N(3)+1.67- atom. The N(2)-N(3) bond length is 1.180 Å. In the third N+1.67- site, N(3)+1.67- is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent La(1)³⁺ and one N(2)+1.67- atom.

KAuSe₂ crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/mbm space group. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a body-centered cubic geometry to eight equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. All K(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 3.548 Å. Au(1)³⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. All Au(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.520 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to four equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Au(1)³⁺ atoms.

Ba₂SrTeO₆ is Orthorhombic Perovskite-derived structured and crystallizes in the trigonal R̅3 space group. Ba(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to nine equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. There are a spread of Ba(1)-O(1) bond distances ranging from 2.790-3.143 Å. Sr(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form SrO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Te(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 17°. All Sr(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.435 Å. Te(1)⁶⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form TeO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Sr(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 17°. All Te(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.963 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ba(1)²⁺, one Sr(1)²⁺, and one Te(1)⁶⁺ atom.

CsCdF₃ is (Cubic) Perovskite structured and crystallizes in the cubic Pm̅3m space group. Cs(1)¹⁺ is bonded to twelve equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form CsF₁₂ cuboctahedra that share corners with twelve equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra, faces with six equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra, and faces with eight equivalent Cd(1)F₆ octahedra. All Cs(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 3.226 Å. Cd(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form CdF₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Cd(1)F₆ octahedra and faces with eight equivalent Cs(1)F₁₂ cuboctahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Cd(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.281 Å. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to four equivalent Cs(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Cd(1)²⁺ atoms.

GaP is Wurtzite structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6₃mc space group. Ga(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing GaP₄ tetrahedra. There are three shorter (2.381 Å) and one longer (2.393 Å) Ga(1)-P(1) bond length. P(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ga(1)³⁺ atoms to form corner-sharing PGa₄ tetrahedra.

CuP₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/c space group. Cu(1)²⁺ is bonded to one P(1)¹⁻ and three equivalent P(2)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted CuP₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Cu(1)P₄ tetrahedra, corners with seven equivalent P(1)CuP₃ tetrahedra, corners with two equivalent P(2)Cu₃P₂ trigonal bipyramids, and  an edgeedge with one Cu(1)P₄ tetrahedra. The Cu(1)-P(1) bond length is 2.268 Å. There are a spread of Cu(1)-P(2) bond distances ranging from 2.320-2.483 Å. There are two inequivalent P¹⁻ sites. In the first P¹⁻ site, P(2)¹⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Cu(1)²⁺ and two equivalent P(1)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted PCu₃P₂ trigonal bipyramids that share corners with two equivalent Cu(1)P₄ tetrahedra, corners with five equivalent P(1)CuP₃ tetrahedra, corners with six equivalent P(2)Cu₃P₂ trigonal bipyramids, and  an edgeedge with one P(2)Cu₃P₂ trigonal bipyramid. There is one shorter (2.206 Å) and one longer (2.227 Å) P(2)-P(1) bond length. In the second P¹⁻ site, P(1)¹⁻ is bonded to one Cu(1)²⁺, one P(1)¹⁻, and two equivalent P(2)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted PCuP₃ tetrahedra that share corners with two equivalent P(1)CuP₃ tetrahedra, corners with seven equivalent Cu(1)P₄ tetrahedra, and corners with five equivalent P(2)Cu₃P₂ trigonal bipyramids. The P(1)-P(1) bond length is 2.213 Å.

Rb₂SiAs₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Ibam space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to six equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms. There are a spread of Rb(1)-As(1) bond distances ranging from 3.556-3.823 Å. Si(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to four equivalent As(1)³⁻ atoms to form distorted edge-sharing SiAs₄ tetrahedra. All Si(1)-As(1) bond lengths are 2.414 Å. As(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to six equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Si(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

RbLiSe is Matlockite structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 5-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. There are four shorter (3.488 Å) and one longer (3.668 Å) Rb(1)-Se(1) bond length. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing LiSe₄ tetrahedra. All Li(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.694 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 9-coordinate geometry to five equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ atoms.
